---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ActionLink from '../components/site/ActionLink.astro';
import FeatureCard from '../components/site/FeatureCard.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/site/PageHeader.astro';
import SplitMedia from '../components/site/SplitMedia.astro';
import philosophyImage from '../assets/img/philosophy.jpg';
import transparencyImage from '../assets/img/transparency.jpg';
import { DISTRIBUTION } from '../consts';
---

<Layout
  title="Philosophy"
  description="Why Amonite exists: every package earns its place by delivering a capability, without redefining Linux."
  image={philosophyImage}
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Philosophy"
    title="Linux should remain Linux. Linux should remain yours."
    lead="Amonite exists so the first day on a new machine delivers real capabilities, without rebuilding the system or giving up ownership of it."
  />

  <article class="mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-20 px-6 py-16 sm:space-y-24 sm:py-20">
    <SplitMedia
      image={philosophyImage}
      alt="Natural form suggesting depth and permanence"
      position="center 35%"
    >
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-graphite sm:text-2xl">
        Why Amonite
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate">
        {DISTRIBUTION.selectionPrinciple}
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate">
        People who choose Linux usually know what it can become. Friction comes earlier: assembling a coherent day-one system from unrelated recommendations.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate">
        Amonite shortens that day. It does not invent a new kind of Linux. It delivers a deliberate set of capabilities and leaves ownership with you.
      </p>
    </SplitMedia>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-graphite sm:text-2xl">
        What makes it different
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate">
        Difference is not a package count. It is a rule for what may ship.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
        <FeatureCard title="Capability over accretion">
          <p>
            Software earns its place by enabling work. Transitive convenience is not enough.
          </p>
        </FeatureCard>
        <FeatureCard title="Replaceability">
          <p>
            Useful on day one must not become a trap on day thirty. Defaults stay open to substitution.
          </p>
        </FeatureCard>
        <FeatureCard title="User ownership">
          <p>
            The person at the keyboard remains in control. The operating system serves that ownership; it does not replace it.
          </p>
        </FeatureCard>
      </div>
    </div>

    <SplitMedia
      image={transparencyImage}
      alt="Clear structure visible through layered material"
      reverse
      aspect="aspect-[5/4]"
    >
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-graphite sm:text-2xl">
        What Amonite does not claim
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate">
        It does not claim to be the fastest, the most secure, or an “AI operating system.” Local AI is one capability among others: desktop, development, administration, networking, and security.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate">
        Technology changes. The selection rule should not.
      </p>
    </SplitMedia>

    <div class="grid gap-8 border border-border bg-sand/15 p-8 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_auto] sm:items-center sm:gap-10 sm:p-10">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-graphite">From principle to capabilities</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate">
          See how day-one work is organized, and how implementation stays subordinate to outcomes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <ActionLink href="/engineering">Engineering</ActionLink>
        <ActionLink href="/downloads" variant="secondary">Downloads</ActionLink>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
